subject: Terrorism
United States Open (Tennis)
Tennis
September 11 (2001)
lead_paragraph: On Saturday, the women’s semifinalists were forced to be second-class citizens because the main arena, Arthur Ashe Stadium, was overbooked after two days of rainouts earlier in the week.
